---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Diogo Guimarães Silva — full-stack developer · ML systems" hero>
  <Fragment slot="hero">
    <h1>Diogo Guimarães Silva</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Full-stack developer · ML systems — Lisbon, Portugal</p>
    <p>
      Three years shipping production web applications, now focused on data and ML systems:
      not just models, but the engineering that makes them trustworthy in production.
    </p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="btn btn-solid" href="/cv/">View CV</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/diogogs">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path
            d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27s1.36.09 2 .27c1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.01 8.01 0 0 0 16 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z"
          ></path></svg>
        GitHub
      </a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/diogo-guimaraes-silva">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path
            d="M20.45 20.45h-3.55v-5.57c0-1.33-.03-3.04-1.85-3.04-1.85 0-2.14 1.45-2.14 2.94v5.67H9.36V9h3.41v1.56h.05c.47-.9 1.63-1.85 3.36-1.85 3.6 0 4.27 2.37 4.27 5.45v6.29zM5.34 7.43a2.06 2.06 0 1 1 0-4.12 2.06 2.06 0 0 1 0 4.12zM7.12 20.45H3.55V9h3.57v11.45zM22.22 0H1.77C.79 0 0 .77 0 1.72v20.55C0 23.22.79 24 1.77 24h20.45c.98 0 1.78-.78 1.78-1.73V1.72C24 .77 23.2 0 22.22 0z"
          ></path></svg>
        LinkedIn
      </a>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <h2>Selected work</h2>

  <div class="card">
    <a
      class="card-media"
      href="https://energia-forecast-bwwhirmyetaphmsk84dkqg.streamlit.app/"
      aria-label="Open the live energia-forecast dashboard"
    >
      <img
        src="/energia-dashboard.png"
        alt="energia-forecast dashboard: tomorrow's demand forecast, model vs baselines"
        width="1280"
        height="800"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </a>
    <div class="card-head">
      <h3>energia-forecast</h3>
      <span class="badge-live">Live</span>
    </div>
    <p class="meta">2026 · personal project · in production</p>
    <p>
      A day-ahead forecasting system for Portuguese electricity demand and MIBEL market
      prices, running autonomously on free-tier infrastructure. Four public data sources
      ingested daily, leakage-free rolling-origin evaluation, conformally calibrated
      intervals, and every forecast stored immutably and scored in public against outcomes.
    </p>
    <div class="stats">
      <div><strong>2.8%</strong><span>demand MAPE (71-day backtest)</span></div>
      <div><strong>13.2 €/MWh</strong><span>price P50 MAE vs 16.0 baseline</span></div>
      <div><strong>€0/mo</strong><span>infrastructure cost</span></div>
    </div>
    <p>
      Built end to end with AI-assisted development (Claude Code), with me as architect and
      reviewer; design decisions recorded as ADRs in the repository.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="https://energia-forecast-bwwhirmyetaphmsk84dkqg.streamlit.app/">Dashboard</a>
      <a href="https://energia-forecast-api.onrender.com/docs">API</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/diogogs/energia-forecast">Source</a>
    </p>
    <div class="tags">
      <span>Python</span><span>LightGBM</span><span>PostgreSQL</span><span>FastAPI</span>
      <span>GitHub Actions</span><span>Streamlit</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-head">
      <h3>dr-watch</h3>
      <span class="badge-live">Live</span>
    </div>
    <p class="meta">2026 · personal project · in production</p>
    <p>
      What did the Portuguese state decide today? An autonomous LLM system over the official
      gazette (Diário da República): every morning it ingests the day's acts, classifies
      them by theme, summarizes each in plain language with citations to the official PDF,
      and publishes a digest whose accuracy is measured continuously — number-grounding
      checks, citation validity, coverage — on a public accuracy page.
    </p>
    <p>
      Same design DNA as energia-forecast, applied to LLM engineering: evals designed before
      prompts, immutable outputs, free-tier strict.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="https://dr-watch-omega.vercel.app/">Site</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/diogogs/dr-watch">Source</a>
    </p>
    <div class="tags">
      <span>Python</span><span>Gemini</span><span>LLM evals</span><span>Next.js</span>
      <span>PostgreSQL</span><span>Vercel</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Experience</h2>

  <div class="band">
    <div class="entry">
      <h3>Software Developer — Bitcliq</h3>
      <p class="meta">September 2023 — present · Caldas da Rainha</p>
      <p>
        Features and full applications across 7+ projects: Flask and Node.js APIs, React and
        C# frontends, React Native, and production debugging for external clients.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="entry">
      <h3>AI Development Intern — Banco BPI (CEIA)</h3>
      <p class="meta">August 2022 — July 2023 · Lisbon</p>
      <p>
        OCR and document-processing tools for financial documents with Python, Tesseract,
        OpenCV and TensorFlow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p><a href="/cv/">Full CV&#160;→</a></p>
  </div>

  <h2>Writing</h2>
  <p>
    I write up what I build. First piece:
    <a href="/posts/the-model-was-the-easy-part/">The model was the easy part</a> — notes
    from building energia-forecast, from backtests that lie by default to the scheduler
    that failed in production. <a href="/posts/">All writing&#160;→</a>
  </p>
</Base>
